Thursday, September 3, 1992

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

92-1558. Sawchyn v. Buckeye Union Ins. Co.

Cuyahoga County, No. 60510. This cause, pending before the court on the filing of a motion for an order directing the Court of Appeals for Cuyahoga County to certify its record and as a claimed appeal as of right from said court, was considered in a manner prescribed by law. On applications of appellees, this cause is hereby dismissed for lack of prosecution pursuant to Section 1, Rule II of the Supreme Court Rules of Practice.
